The QUADRANGLE, eventually deformed, is defined from
the 4 lines which define its 4 edges.

ATTENTION: The 4 lines must be given with a consecutive order or not
           --------L3---------
           |                 |  
          L4                 L2
           |                 |
           --------L1---------    
ATTENTION:   
The number of sub-quadrangles will be equal to the product M x N where
M is the number of edges of the line 1 equal to the number of edges of the line 3
N is the number of edges of the line 2 equal to the number of edges of the line 4

Example: S1; I; 1; L1; L2; L3; L4;
Define a quadrangulation of contour the edges of lines L1 L2 L3 L4 
